result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Emily Jeanne Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Edward Minser DF ATTY: Mandy Lynn Caffee, DF: Emily Jeanne Anderson appeared.  Court called at 3:58 p.m.  State files DJOC with the Court.  Attorneys stipulate to the  oral amendment of 2 additional misdemeanor counts added to the charges.  State will file amended Information after sentencing.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights.   Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalties.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct 1., Ct. 2 & Ct. 3.  Court reviews the police reports.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and stays the Ct. 1 conviction upon the full performance of the DJOC.  Crt finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudicated Guilty to Ct. 2 & Ct. 3.  Crt orders the State to provide the DE an amended Information within 24 hours.     Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement.  Crt orders:

Ct. 1 in 14CF458
- DJOC will be for 3 years and is approved and signed by the court

Ct. 2 & Ct. 3 in 14CF458 to run concurrent
- W/S 2 years probation with conditions
- DE is to fully comply with the DJOC and all provisions
- Restitution in the amount of $4,762.70 to be paid at the rate of $200 a month beginning September 1, 2015 through DOC
- It is hereby ordered, the defendant have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Carol or Laverne L.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  
- 100 hours community service
- Court costs on Ct. 2 $243 and court costs on Ct. 3 $243 to be paid through the DOC 
- DE to report to probation within the next 24 hours
- Bail is continued until DE signs up for probation
- 20 days to appeal
Plea/sentencing hearing at 08-26-2015 04:00 pm

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Carol or Laverne L.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
